Andropogon gerardii var. gerardii

   [3203.jpg]
    Authority   Vitman
      Family    Liliopsida:Commelinidae:Cyperales:Gramineae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 3203

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A bunchgrass with abundant leaves, reaching a height
   of 1-2 m. USES It is used for pastue and hay. GROWING PERIOD Perennial
   grass. COMMON NAMES Big bluestem, Turkeyfoot grass. FURTHER INF Big
   bluestem is a North American prairie grass usually found on loamy
   soils.

   Sources
   SOURCES (A. gerardii Vitman)
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 141 [USE]
   Duke J 1979 pp 94 [PH, RAIN, TEMP]
   Duke J 1975 pp 6 [PH, RAIN, TEMP]
   Heath M 1985 pp 180 [TEXT, USE]

